pamsignal (0.3.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * NEW: detect failed sudo/su password attempts and emit a
    brute-force alert when the per-actor threshold is crossed.
    pam_unix authentication-failure messages are now parsed; the
    tracker keys by source IP when rhost is set (covers SSH→sudo
    chains) and by ruser otherwise. Per-event chat alerts are
    suppressed for sudo/su login failures so a single mistyped
    password does not spam Telegram/Slack.
  * BREAKING: daemon binary moves from /usr/bin/pamsignal to
    /usr/sbin/pamsignal (FHS §4.10). dpkg handles the relocation
    atomically on upgrade; the unit's ExecStart is updated in
    lockstep via meson configure_file. Update any scripts that
    reference the absolute /usr/bin/pamsignal path.
  * BREAKING: legacy PAMSIGNAL_* journal fields removed. Saved
    journalctl queries need PAMSIGNAL_EVENT=LOGIN_FAILED →
    EVENT_ACTION=login_failure (and similar for the rest of the
    set; see CHANGELOG.md for the full mapping).
  * Packaging cleanup: meson now installs the systemd unit to the
    vendor path reported by pkg-config; ExecStart is templated via
    configure_file. debian/rules drops the post-install mv/sed
    workarounds that relocated the unit and rewrote ExecStart at
    package-build time.
  * Add a section-8 man page (pamsignal.8). Installed and
    auto-compressed by dh_compress; verified by the test-deb CI
    job after install and after purge.
  * Security: close two clang-analyzer taint-source warnings
    (taint into __ctype_b_loc table from isspace() and tainted
    malloc size from getgroups). No exploitable vulnerabilities
    closed; both were defensive narrowings.
  * Docs: docs/deployment.md Install and Uninstall sections split
    by install path (apt / dnf / source build). Documents apt
    remove vs apt purge semantics and the .rpmsave behavior.

 -- Tuan Nguyen <anhtuank7c@hotmail.com>  Sun, 03 May 2026 14:00:00 +0000

pamsignal (0.2.4-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add optional server context tags (provider, service_name) to alert
    payloads. When configured in pamsignal.conf they are appended to
    chat-text alerts and injected under the ECS labels.* dictionary in
    JSON webhook payloads.
  * docs: TypeScript Express webhook receiver example and Bruno test
    collection; expand custom-webhook integration docs.
  * ci(test-deb): drive the functional test with real sshd auth events
    instead of `logger -t sshd` (the v0.2.3 _EXE allowlist drops the
    latter).
  * ci: pin `environment: release` on every release job so secrets
    (GPG_*) resolve consistently.

 -- Tuan Nguyen <anhtuank7c@hotmail.com>  Sun, 03 May 2026 07:00:00 +0000

pamsignal (0.2.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Security: enforce a _EXE allowlist on every journal entry so
    unprivileged users can no longer inject fake PAM events via
    logger(1) to trigger false alerts or brute-force lockouts. Only
    entries whose _EXE resolves to sshd / sudo / su / login /
    systemd-logind under a system prefix are processed; entries with a
    missing _EXE are dropped.
  * Fix brute-force tracker: zero last_brute_alert_usec on the
    evict-and-reuse path so a new IP doesn't inherit the evicted IP's
    alert cooldown.
  * Fix SIGHUP reload: preserve the in-memory brute-force tracking
    table across reloads instead of zeroing it. Existing per-IP attempt
    counts and cooldowns survive a config reload.

 -- Tuan Nguyen <anhtuank7c@hotmail.com>  Sat, 02 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000

